  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve monitoring and evaluation frameworks, capacity, and use in supported developing countries for improved evidence-informed policy making.

The Global Evaluation Initiative (GEI) is a coalition of major development partners with the purpose of improving M&amp;E capacities in developing countries to improvement evidence-based policy to rebuild better and reach the 2030 goals. Key partners are the WB (holding the Secretariat), UNDP, Canada, Finland, Sweden, Germany, the Netherlands, Norway, Switzerland and multilaterals such as IADB and IFAD. The initiative will be implemented with a first 5-years work programme 2021-2025, currently with USD 20 mill. committed for the Trust Fund (see https://www.globalevaluationinitiative.org/)</narrative>
  </description>
